emor, prostration with coarse whole body tremor, elevated body temperature, coma, and death. Paresthesia, severe corneal damage, hypotension and tachycardia, associated with anaphylaxis, can also occur following pyrethriod poisoning. (L857)'),(248,248,'Pyrethroid effects typically include rapid onset of aggressive behavior and increased sensitivity to external stimuli, followed by fine tremor, prostration with coarse whole body tremor, elevated body temperature, coma, and death. Paresthesia, severe corneal damage, hypotension and tachycardia, associated with anaphylaxis, can also occur following pyrethriod poisoning. (L857)'),(249,249,'At high doses, signs of poisoning attributable to cyfluthrin include profuse salivation and pulmonary edema, clonic seizures, opisthotonos (i.e., the spine is bent forward such that a supine body rests on its head and heels), coma, and death. At lower doses, commonly observed effects include paresthesia and erythema. As for other type 2 pyrethroids,  cyfluthrin produces a severe syndrome characterized by salivation and choreoathetosis. (L863)'),(250,250,'At high doses, signs of poisoning attributable to cyhalothrin include profuse salivation and pulmonary edema, clonic seizures, opisthotonos (i.e., the spine is bent forward such that a supine body rests on its head and heels), coma, and death. At lower doses, commonly observed effects include paresthesia and erythema. (L863)'),(251,251,'At high doses, signs of poisoning attributable to cypermethrin include profuse salivation and pulmonary edema, clonic seizures, opisthotonos (i.e., the spine is bent forward such that a supine body rests on its head and heels), coma, and death. At lower doses, commonly observed effects include paresthesia and erythema (L863).'),(252,252,'At high doses, signs of poisoning attributable to deltamethrin include profuse salivation and pulmonary edema, clonic seizures, opisthotonos (i.e., the spine is bent forward such that a supine body rests on its head and heels), coma, and death. At lower doses, commonly observed effects include paresthesia and erythema (L863).'),(253,253,'At high doses, signs of poisoning attributable to esfenvalerate include profuse salivation and pulmonary edema, clonic seizures, opisthotonos (i.e., the spine is bent forward such that a supine body rests on its head and heels), coma, and death. At lower doses, commonly observed effects include paresthesia and erythema. (L863)'),(254,254,'Avermectins are neurotoxic and have reproductive and developmental effects. (L1826)'),(255,255,'Nitromethylenes are neurotoxic. (T10)'),(256,256,'Nitromethylenes are neurotoxic. (T10)'),(257,257,'Nitromethylenes are neurotoxic. (T10)'),(258,258,'Coronary spasm, hypotension, and sinus tachycardia may occur following exposure. Aspiration of insecticide containing petroleum\ndistillate may result in pneumonitis. Pancreatitis can result from ingestion. (T36). '),(259,259,'Health effects of metolachlor include CNS depression, dizziness, dyspnea, liver damage, nephritis, cardiovascular failure,  and adverse reproductive effects. (A571)'),(260,260,'Eye exposure may cause corneal damage. Erythematopapular contact eczema can follow exposure to propachlor. (L904, L905)'),(261,261,'The health effects of the different barium compounds depend on how well the compound dissolves in water or the stomach contents. At low doses, barium acts as a muscle stimulant, while higher doses affect the nervous system, causing cardiac irregularities, tremors, weakness, anxiety, dyspnea, paralysisand possibly death. Barium may also cause gastrointestinal disturbances, damage the kidneys and cause decreases in body weight. (L214)'),(262,262,'The health effects of the different barium compounds depend on how well the compound dissolves in water or the stomach contents. At low doses, barium acts as a muscle stimulant, while higher doses affect the nervous system, causing cardiac irregularities, tremors, weakness, anxiety, dyspnea, paralysisand 